!! Fonts
URxvt*font: xft:FONT:medium:style=Regular:size=FONT_SIZE

URxvt*boldFont: xft:FONT:bold:size=FONT_SIZE
URxvt*italicFont: xft:FONT:italic::size=FONT_SIZE
URxvt*boldItalicFont: xft:FONT:bold:italic:size=FONT_SIZE

!URxvt*internalBorder: FONT_PAD
URxvt.letterSpace: LETTER_SPACE
URxvt.lineSpace: LINE_SPACE

! :Bind C-0, C-+ and C-= to activate small, medium, and big font size resp.
! This is not akin to zoom in or out, but only 3 sizes, which is all Dina has.
! NOTE variables do not seem to be expanded in the below format. Uknown why.

! Need to understand how commands in urxvt work... cuz these can be hotkeys for
putting text in terminal too. Found this out while trying double quotes around
the entire \033 to \007

URxvt.keysym.C-0: command:\033]710;-*-*-medium-r-normal-*-8-*-*-*-*-*-*-*\007
URxvt.keysym.C-minus: command:\033]710;-*-*-medium-r-normal-*-7-*-*-*-*-*-*-*\007
URxvt.keysym.C-equal: command:\033]710;-*-*-medium-r-normal-*-16-*-*-*-*-*-*-*\007
URxvt.keysym.C-plus: command:\033]710;-*-*-medium-r-normal-*-20-*-*-*-*-*-*-*\007
